                        h2 What is knowledge management?
                        p.lead
                            | Knowledge management (KM) is the method of systematic organisation, creation, utilisation, and sharing of collective intelligence or knowledge within an organisation. Successful knowledge management ensures that information is securely stored in a readily accessible location.

        section.bg-light
            .container.px-4
